But recognized that logical short-circuiting is a common Python idiom and found in React. Just not convinced that because one can, and does, that one should.

Using logical short-circuiting does **not** provide a performance benefit when compared to using a ternary operator in this situation. For reference, see sections [12.13.3](https://www.ecma-international.org/publications/files/ECMA-ST/Ecma-262.pdf) and [12.14.3](https://www.ecma-international.org/publications/files/ECMA-ST/Ecma-262.pdf).

