Eratosthenes Sieve is a much better approach to finding coprimes:
- create a bitmask of length `n`, filled with 0s;
- starting with `i = 2`:
  - if `mask[i]` is 1 then continue;
  - if `n` is divisible by `i`, then set all elements of the bitmask that are multiples of `i` to 1;
- continue until `i*i < n`.
In the end, all elements of bitmask that are 0s are coprime to `n`.

